h-500x500.jpg 500w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/butter-cookie-dough.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"h-tips-for-making-butter-cookies\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTips for Making Butter Cookies:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe dough will be soft before freezing, so if you are rolling it out to make cutout shapes (like I have in these photos), be sure to use more flour than the recipe card calls for. This will be for dusting the surface and the rolling pin. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eI used \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/3Asg0D0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"\u003ecookie stamps\u003c/a\u003e to create designs. \u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eYou could also use a \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/3TIUdxG\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"\u003ecookie press gun\u003c/a\u003e or \u003ca href=\"https://amzn.to/3TL7upr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"\u003ecookie stamp roller\u003c/a\u003e to create designs.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eAnother traditional method is to pipe dough using large pastry tips. I don’t recommend this method. Even if your dough is very soft, it takes a lot of hand strength to do this method. Maybe for some it works great, but I’ve never had success with it. \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1200\" data-pin-url=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/butter-cookies-6-ingredients/?tp_image_id=99035\" data-pin-title=\"easy butter cookies\" src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/pipe-the-dough.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/pipe-the-dough.jpg 1200w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/pipe-the-dough-150x150.jpg 150w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/pipe-the-dough-300x300.jpg 300w, https://a